With the latest 'develop' version, using the latest VS2012 Project Template in WinRT, I tried the following:

``` javascript
_graphics.GraphicsDevice.SetRenderTarget(buffer);

            _graphics.GraphicsDevice.Clear(Color.Transparent);

            _graphics.GraphicsDevice.DepthStencilState = DepthStencilState.Default;

            foreach (ModelMesh mesh in model.Meshes)
            {
                foreach (BasicEffect effect in mesh.Effects)
                {
                    effect.EnableDefaultLighting();
                    effect.PreferPerPixelLighting = true;

                    effect.World = Matrix.Identity;
                    effect.View = Matrix.CreateLookAt(Vector3.Backward * 100.0f, Vector3.Zero, Vector3.Up);
                    effect.Projection = Matrix.CreatePerspectiveFieldOfView(MathHelper.PiOver4, GraphicsDevice.Viewport.AspectRatio, 1.0f, 1000.0f);

                    effect.DiffuseColor = Color.White.ToVector3();
                }

                mesh.Draw();
            }

            _graphics.GraphicsDevice.SetRenderTarget(null);

            GraphicsDevice.Clear(Color.Black);

            _spriteBatch.Begin(SpriteSortMode.Immediate, BlendState.AlphaBlend);
            _spriteBatch.Draw(buffer, Vector2.Zero, Color.White);
            _spriteBatch.End();
```

The model renders just fine on its own directly in the backbuffer, but with the code above, the model renders into the RenderTarget2D (buffer) only once (first frame) and never again. Can anyone else verify this?
